Definition

A Context Window is the maximum amount of information (measured in tokens) that an LLM can remember and use while generating a response.

Real-world Analogy

Think of a whiteboard with limited space. Once it becomes full, you must erase older information to write something new.

Salesforce Example

If an AI Assistant reads multiple Apex classes, Flows, and Object Metadata that exceed the context window, older information may be discarded unless Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) is used.

